    "John Trapp": "Let them marry ] There is no lust so hot and violent, but God\u2019s medicines rightly applied will cool and heal. Only remember that it is not the having, but the loving of a wife that keepeth a man chaste and clean. And that God doth use to correct excess and dalliance between married couples, with strong temptations after strange flesh. Better to marry than burn ] As an oven heated by the baker, #Ho 7:4 . As those pagans were scalded, #Ro 1:27 , and these papagans { a } still are, that are forbidden to marry, and yet cannot contain. { a } Papist, Popish (with allusion to pagan). \u0152D\nVer.\n9. Let them marry] There is no lust so hot and violent, but God\u2019s medicines rightly applied will cool and heal. Only remember that it is not the having, but the loving of a wife that keepeth a man chaste and clean. And that God doth use to correct excess and dalliance between married couples, with strong temptations after strange flesh. Better to marry than burn] As an oven heated by the baker, #Ho [v_Rom_1_27] 7:",
